# Add CVE/check IDs here with a one-line comment per entry explaining why suppressed.

# AVD-AWS-0132: SSE-S3 (AES256) is acceptable for these buckets — personal
# infra with no compliance requirement for customer-managed KMS keys; the
# per-CMK monthly cost and per-request KMS calls aren't justified here.
AVD-AWS-0132

# guide.eic-seminarios.com is a deliberately PUBLIC static-website bucket
# (origin for the guide CloudFront distribution). Its public-access-block is
# intentionally permissive and a public-read bucket policy is required, so the
# four S3 public-access checks below are expected and suppressed for this repo.
# AVD-AWS-0086: public access block does not block public ACLs.
AVD-AWS-0086
# AVD-AWS-0087: public access block does not block public policies.
AVD-AWS-0087
# AVD-AWS-0091: public access block does not ignore public ACLs.
AVD-AWS-0091
# AVD-AWS-0093: public access block does not restrict public buckets.
AVD-AWS-0093

# AVD-AWS-0011: the guide CloudFront distribution has no WAF — it serves a
# public, static documentation site with no sensitive data; a WAF web ACL's
# monthly cost isn't justified for this personal-infra use case.
AVD-AWS-0011
